reviewText: Why not have, in the listing of a given item, details on what the item IS?!  I have many Milton Berle shows;  I'm looking for more.  But, if the manufacturer fails to supply any facts concerning dates, cast, and content, there's no way of telling if I already have the episodes in question or not. So, unless I feel like gambling, I pass on purchasing. Far too many listings of books and other media items actively discourage sales by not telling potential buyers exactly what they would be getting.
